File: Lemons seen hanging from a tree. Pixabay/Pexels JOHANNESBURG - Good news for lemon exporters. The Far East is being seen as a major future market for South Africa. WATCH: SONA 2022 | Unpacking Ramaphosa's address Agriculture Minister Thoko Didiza has seen off a consignment of about 100,000 lemons destined for China. The fruit was exported under a new protocol signed in September last year. READ: China exports surge in 2021 as global demand picks up South Africa's also signed a protocol with China for the export of pears in December. This seems to support President Cyril Ramaphosa announcement during his State of the Nation Address that the agricultural sector has significant potential for job creation.